stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    state "Start" as Init
    state "Credit Note Creation" as CN_Create
    state "Awaiting Approval" as CN_Approval
    state "Credit Note Approved" as CN_Approved
    state "Credit Note Issued" as CN_Issued
    state "Refund Decision" as Refund_Decision
    state "Refund Initiated" as Refund_Initiate
    state "Refund Processing (Payment Gateway)" as Refund_PGW
    state "Refund Failed" as Refund_Failed
    state "Refund Completed" as Refund_Complete
    state "End" as End

    [*] --> Init: Customer Request / System Trigger

    Init --> CN_Create: Agent creates Credit Note in CRM
    note on CN_Create
        **CRM Action**:
        - Link to original Invoice/Order ID.
        - Specify items, quantity, reason for credit.
        - Auto-calculates credit amount.
        - Sets initial status to 'Draft'.
    end note

    CN_Create --> CN_Approval: Submit for Approval
    CN_Create --> End: Cancel Credit Note Draft (No further action)

    CN_Approval --> CN_Approved: Manager Approves (Policy Check)
    note on CN_Approval
        **CRM Action**:
        - Manager/Supervisor reviews details against policy.
        - Approval logs user, date, and reason.
        - Updates CN status to 'Approved'.
    end note

    CN_Approval --> CN_Create: Manager Rejects / Requests Revision (Back to Draft)

    CN_Approved --> CN_Issued: Credit Note Finalized & Issued
    note on CN_Issued
        **CRM Action**:
        - Generates official Credit Note document (PDF).
        - Updates customer's account balance/ledger.
        - Integrates with accounting system.
        - Emails Credit Note to customer.
        - Updates CN status to 'Issued'.
    end note

    CN_Issued --> Refund_Decision: Determine Refund Type
    CN_Issued --> End: Credit Applied to Customer Account (No monetary refund)

    Refund_Decision --> Refund_Initiate: Monetary Refund Required
    note on Refund_Decision
        **CRM Logic**:
        - Based on return policy (e.g., cash refund vs. store credit).
        - Customer preference for refund method.
        - Checks original payment method eligibility for refund.
    end note

    Refund_Initiate --> Refund_PGW: Send Refund Request to Payment Gateway
    note on Refund_Initiate
        **CRM Action**:
        - Records refund request details (amount, method, requested date).
        - Initiates API call to integrated Payment Gateway.
        - Updates CN/Refund status to 'Pending Payment Gateway'.
    end note

    Refund_PGW --> Refund_Complete: Payment Gateway Confirms Success
    note on Refund_PGW
        **External System**:
        - Payment Gateway processes the actual refund transaction.
        - Sends success/failure callback to CRM.
    end note

    Refund_PGW --> Refund_Failed: Payment Gateway Reports Failure

    Refund_Complete --> End: Customer Notified / Flow Concluded
    note on Refund_Complete
        **CRM Action**:
        - Updates order/invoice status to 'Refunded'.
        - Records refund transaction ID and actual refund date.
        - Sends refund confirmation email to customer.
        - Finalizes CN/Refund status to 'Completed'.
    end note

    Refund_Failed --> Refund_Initiate: Agent Retries Refund (if applicable)
    note on Refund_Failed
        **CRM Action**:
        - Alerts agent for manual follow-up.
        - Logs error message and reason from Payment Gateway.
        - Allows for re-attempt or manual intervention.
    end note

    Refund_Failed --> End: Manual Resolution / Escalation (e.g., check via bank transfer)